	<h3>How to use</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>On the inspect section you can open (by clicking the button or drag-dropping the file directly from your computer onto the same button) and see all the entries on an icon file (being entries it's different images in their different sizes).</li>
		<li>On the build section you can add images (click to select a file or drop one or several files over the same button) to build your icon. Every image entry will have the option to choose the resolution which the image will be stored in the icon file (it's advisable to scale your images with third party programs if possible, as they offer better scaling algorithms than the browser). Once you added all of your images you can input the filename to download at the right of the "Total entries" title, and click export to download the compiled file.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<h3>Limitations</h3>
	<ul>
		<li>When inspecting icons, entries with lower than 32bpp color depth fail to display the entry's image.</li>
		<li>All icons are exported with 32bpp color depth.</li>
		<li>Works under Google Chrome and Firefox.</li>
		<li>Known issue: On Firefox, BMP icon entries with transparency are displayed with black background insted of a transparent one.</li>
		<li>Known issue: On Firefox, the Icon filename textbox value is ignored when saving the forged icon file.</li>
	</ul>
	
